Class MVIClassifier

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, Serializable, AutoCloseable, IClassifier<double[]>, IFixableClassifier<double[]>, IFixedClassifier<double[]>, ITaggedEntity

    public class MVIClassifier
extends AbstractFixableFeatureGramClassifier
implements IFixableClassifier<double[]>, Closeable
    A trainable classifier that uses a Maximo Visual Insights (MVI) server, via MVIFeatureGramClassifier instance, to train and classify. Labeled feature extraction is done in this instance, the resulting feature grams are managed by an instance of MVIFeatureGramClassifier. The model is then trained from this instance against those stored spectrograms producing a model identifier that can be used for classification of similar features. The bulk of the behavior/configuration is controlled and enabled by #MVIFeatureGramClassifier and as such you should consult the docs there.

    A name may be assigned to the models and datasets and trained models and datasets can be preserved across instances. As such, new instances can use a past name to connect to a pre-trained model, and even a currently deployed model.

    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • MVIClassifier

        public MVIClassifier()
        Convenience on #MVIClassifier(IFeatureGramDescriptor) using the default feature gram extractor that preserves the models. Requires VAPI_HOST/VAPI_PORT or VAPI_BASE_URI and VAPI_TOKEN env vars to be set to point to the MVI server and set the API key for that server.

      • MVIClassifier

        public MVIClassifier(IFeatureGramDescriptor<double[],double[]> featureGramExtractor,
                     String name,
                     boolean preserveModel)
        Create and use env variables (VAPI_HOST/VAPI_BASE_URI , VAPI_TOKEN and optionally VAPI_PORT (defaults to 443)) to define location of MVI server.
        Parameters:
        featureGramExtractor -
        the - name to use for data sets and models. If null, one is generated.
        preserveModel - if true, then leave the most recent data set and trained model on the server.

      • MVIClassifier

        public MVIClassifier(IFeatureGramDescriptor<double[],double[]> featureGramExtractor,
                     String name,
                     boolean preserveModel,
                     String mviHost,
                     int mviPort,
                     String mviApiKey,
                     List<MVIAugmentation> augList)
        Parameters:
        featureGramExtractor -
        preserveModel - if true, then leave the most recent data set and trained model on the server.
        the - name to use for data sets and models. If null or empty, one is generated.
        mviHost - if null, then use VAPI_HOST or VAPI_BASE_URI env var value.
        mviPort - if 0 or less and VAPI_BASE_URI is not set, then use VAPI_PORT env var value. Defaults to 443 and so https.
        mviApiKey - if null, then use VAPI_TOKEN env var value.
        augList - option list of augmentations. Can be null or empty.
